							<h1>Forum for Industrial Interaction</h1>
							<p>Forum for Industrial Interaction (FII),  the face of IIMB in the corporate world, is a student-run initiative. The 41-member team's goal is to promote interaction between academia, industry and the government to complement and enhance learning at IIMB. FII is the only organizing body which has the mandate to organize Business-related events at an inter-college level. FII organizes and conducts major events on campus throughout the year. The flagship event is Vista, a business festival that attracts participants from over 350 colleges and over 60 companies. Other events include: Hell-Square (an intra-college event), Nexus (a public policy debating event modeled on MUN), Colloquiums (a series of lectures running through the year) & TEDxIIMBangalore.</p></div>
